CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 15, 1947, pg. 8, reads: "Bride! - The brand new bride, Mrs. Henry Hereford, smiles for The Courier photographer and thinks what a quickie she pulled on fellow workers at the plant this weekend when she slipped away to Baltimore and married. The groom is a resident of Rankin, the former home of the bride, who was Miss Gladys Wylie. Attending the bride was Mrs. Cleopatra Dixon, while the groom had Atty. Alfred Hughes as best man. Attending the ceremony were Mr. and Mrs. Oswald Crains of New York, close friends of the bride. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Gladys Wylie Hereford wearing top with tied bows on front and large brooch, posed in front of dark curtain, in Harris Studio
